  "texts": [
    "We represent crystal structures using their c-axis coordinates as atom vectors for distinction.",
    "When replacing x S atoms with O atoms, the final x bits of the vector are utilized to denote the position of the O atom, while the initial 14-x bits indicate the position of the S atom.",
    "This encoding method efficiently utilizes 14 non-negative numbers to differentiate between distinct structures.",
    "(All atom vectors data is provided in Supplementary Data 1).",
    "Figure 5b illustrates the optimal synthesis route, where the gray spheres represent S atoms, and the blue spheres represent O atoms."
